5000|$|Steam {{locomotives}} {{normally have}} at least two double acting cylinders, which enables the cranks to be set so that at least one piston will always be off the <b>dead</b> <b>centre</b> and no starting assistance is required. In the common case of a two piston locomotive, the cranks are set at right angles, so that whenever one piston is at <b>dead</b> <b>centre</b> the other is in mid-stroke, and giving four equally spaced power strokes per revolution.|$|R
