50|$|Squish is {{an effect}} in {{internal}} combustion engines which creates sudden turbulence of the fuel/air mixture as the piston approaches top <b>dead</b> <b>centre</b> (TDC).|$|R
50|$|Process 4-1 {{completes the}} cycle by a constant-volume {{process in which}} heat is {{rejected}} from the air while the piston is at bottom <b>dead</b> <b>centre.</b>|$|R
